---
export const title = 'Variants';
export const order = 200;
import DemoComponentCard from '../../../../components/DemoComponentCard.astro';
---
<p class='text-body-large'>The button group supports two layout variants: <strong>standard</strong> (buttons with a gap) and <strong>connected</strong> (buttons with a 2px gap; outer buttons have fully rounded outer corners, middle buttons keep standard rounded corners).</p>

<p class='text-body-large'><strong>Standard</strong> — buttons are independent with a visible gap between them.</p>
<DemoComponentCard lang={'html'}>
  <wc-button-group>
    <wc-button>First</wc-button>
    <wc-button>Second</wc-button>
    <wc-button>Third</wc-button>
  </wc-button-group>
</DemoComponentCard>

<p class='text-body-large'><strong>Connected</strong> — buttons share a 2px gap; outer buttons have fully rounded outer corners and middle buttons use standard rounded corners.</p>
<DemoComponentCard lang={'html'}>
  <wc-button-group connected>
    <wc-button toggle>First</wc-button>
    <wc-button toggle>Second</wc-button>
    <wc-button toggle>Third</wc-button>
  </wc-button-group>
</DemoComponentCard>

<p class='text-body-large'>Connected variant also works with icon buttons.</p>
<DemoComponentCard lang={'html'}>
  <wc-button-group connected>
    <wc-icon-button toggle><wc-icon name='format_bold'></wc-icon></wc-icon-button>
    <wc-icon-button toggle><wc-icon name='format_italic'></wc-icon></wc-icon-button>
    <wc-icon-button toggle><wc-icon name='format_underlined'></wc-icon></wc-icon-button>
  </wc-button-group>
</DemoComponentCard>

<style is:inline>
  strong {
    font-weight: bold;
  }
</style>
